trend_summary: Across the sequence the island keeps its grid of detached houses, but vacant lots steadily infill, boat docks multiply, and tree cover thins. Shorelines migrate, with visible erosion on the west and new sediment on the southeast tip. Overall built-up fabric tightens yet remains predominantly low-rise suburban housing.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of vacant residential lots, raising roof density.
Expansion of private docks and marina facilities along the northern shore.
Noticeable loss of tree canopy in central blocks, replaced by structures or paved areas.
Erosion on the western shoreline; simultaneous accretion and new land on the southeast tip.
Minor road realignments and widening near the central causeway entrance.
